"Dr Louis de Wecke": Your hands are steady, Señor Rizal. Ophthalmology requires patience and precision.
Rizal: My mother is losing her eyesight. I wish to help people like her.
"Dr Louis de Wecke": A noble reason to become a doctor.
Rizal: Knowledge is the best way I can serve my family and my country.
"european scholar": Rizal, you study medicine and literature at the same time?
Rizal: A nation needs both science and ideas to move forward.
"Maximo Viola": Jose, the manuscript is finished?
Rizal: Yes. This novel tells the truth about the suffering of Filipinos.
"Maximo Viola": Then it must be published.
Rizal: Printing it will anger powerful people.
"Maximo Viola": Truth is worth the risk. I will help pay for the printing.
Rizal: Thank you, my friend. This book must reach the world.
"Printing Master": The press is ready. Once we begin, there is no turning back.
Rizal: Then let the truth be printed.